author: stsp
msg: On the fs-successor-ids branch, write successor-IDs during commit.
The file formats used in this initial implementation are described here:
https://svn.apache.org/repos/asf/subversion/branches/fs-successor-ids/BRANCH-README?p=1165719
They are subject to change as the design evolves.
* subversion/libsvn_fs_fs/fs_fs.c
(): Include apr_want.h to get htonl() and ntohl() declarations.
(FSFS_SUCCESSORS_MAX_FILES_PER_DIR,
FSFS_SUCCESSOR_IDS_END_MARKER): New constants.
(FSFS_SUCCESSORS_REV_OFFSET): New helper macro.
(path_successor_ids, path_successor_revisions,
path_successor_node_revs, copy_file_partially): New helper functions.
(update_successor_ids_file, update_successor_revisions_file,
update_successor_node_revs_files): New functions which write successor
map data in the format described in the design proposal linked above.
(update_successor_map): New function which writes new successor IDs
to the filesystem in an atomic fashion (moving temporary files into place).
(commit_body): Write successor data to the filesystem before updating
the 'current' file.
